ess the structure and properties of materials and surfaces. When light, sound, or some other wave energy is directed at the material in question, "imperfections" in the resulting echo can reveal a tremendous amount of valuable diagnostic information. The mathematics behind such analysis is sophisticated and complex. However, while problems involving stationary materials are quite well understood, there is still much to learn about those in which the material is moving or changes over time. These so-called non-autonomous problems are the subject of this fascinating book. Roach develops practical strategies, techniques, and solutions for mathematicians and applied scientists working in or seeking entry into the field of modern scattering theory and its applications. Wave Scattering by Time-Dependent Perturbations is destined to become a classic in this rapidly evolving area of inquiry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aPerturbation (Mathematics). 0aScattering (Physics)xMathematics. 0aWavesxMathematics. 7aSCIENCE / Waves & Wave Mechanics.2bisacsh  aAcoustic wave equation.  aAcoustic wave.  aAffine space.  aAngular frequency.  aApproximation.  aAsymptotic analysis.  aAsymptotic expansion.  aBanach space.  aBasis (linear algebra).  aBessel's inequality.  aBoundary value problem.  aBounded operator.  aC0-semigroup.  aCalculation.  aCharacteristic function (probability theory).  aClassical physics.  aCodimension.  aCoefficient.  aContinuous function (set theory).  aContinuous function.  aContinuous spectrum.  aConvolution.  aDifferentiable function.  aDifferential equation.  aDimension (vector space).  aDimension.  aDimensional analysis.  aDirac delta function.  aDirichlet problem.  aDistribution (mathematics).  aDuhamel's principle.  aEigenfunction.  aEi